		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've written a rudimentary test for support, it's at <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://eamp.org/li/nrom368.zip">http://eamp.org/li/nrom368.zip</a><!-- m --> . It contains an iNES file to demonstrate what it will look like when only the top 32kB are decoded, as well as the CHR and expanded PRG (where ROM A15 = nPRGSEL) for placing on a devcart. If implemented correctly, the center of the screen should be full of white symbols (HZ or âœ“) and no red (X or M).
<br />
<br />To repeat: the iNES file does NOT contain the full 48-or-64kB image both because FCEU(X) behaves differently from the other emulators I've tried and would not work and because I don't want to cast a vote on the layout inside an iNES file.

		

